@baseUrl = http://localhost:8000/api
@accessToken = paste_access_token_here
@shopSlug = ama-thrift
@logoPath = C:\Users\User\Pictures\shop-logo.jpg
@bannerPath = C:\Users\User\Pictures\shop-banner.jpg

### Create DigiShop with hosted image URLs
POST {{baseUrl}}/digishops
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shopName": "Ama Thrift",
  "bio": "Curated thrift finds from Accra.",
  "logoUrl": "https://example.com/logo.jpg",
  "bannerUrl": "https://example.com/banner.jpg",
  "category": "both",
  "instagram": "https://instagram.com/amathrift",
  "whatsapp": "+233501234567"
}

### Create DigiShop with image upload
POST {{baseUrl}}/digishops
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: multipart/form-data; boundary=FormBoundary

--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="shopName"

Ama Thrift
--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="bio"

Curated thrift finds from Accra.
--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="category"

both
--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="instagram"

https://instagram.com/amathrift
--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="whatsapp"

+233501234567
--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="logo"; filename="shop-logo.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< {{logoPath}}
--FormBoundary
Content-Disposition: form-data; name="banner"; filename="shop-banner.jpg"
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< {{bannerPath}}
--FormBoundary--

### Get my DigiShop
GET {{baseUrl}}/digishops/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}

### Update my DigiShop
PUT {{baseUrl}}/digishops/me
Authorization: Bearer {{accessToken}}
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "shopName": "Ama Thrift",
  "bio": "Updated bio for curated thrift finds.",
  "category": "retail",
  "instagram": "https://instagram.com/amathrift",
  "whatsapp": "+233501234567"
}

### Public shop by slug
GET {{baseUrl}}/digishops/{{shopSlug}}
